        <h2>OUR TIPS FOR WINNERS</h2>
        <div class="card-container">
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Drink Plenty of Water</h3>
                <p>Drinking enough water is essential for maintaining proper body function. It helps regulate body temperature, flush out toxins, and aids digestion. Staying hydrated also improves skin health and boosts energy levels. Aim to drink at least eight glasses of water a day to support your overall health.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Eat Colorful Vegetables</h3>
                <p>Vegetables come in a variety of colors, each representing different nutrients and health benefits. Eating a colorful variety ensures that you get a wide range of vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. Aim to include red, orange, yellow, green, and purple vegetables in your diet to boost your immune system and maintain optimal health.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Choose Whole Grains</h3>
                <p>Whole grains are a great source of fiber, which is important for digestive health and maintaining a healthy weight. They are rich in essential vitamins and minerals, including iron, magnesium, and B vitamins. Opt for whole grain foods like oats, brown rice, quinoa, and whole wheat bread to improve your heart health and stabilize your blood sugar levels.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        
    
